u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-IRAQ-MIDEAST-REVIEW-N     11-28 1166
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IRAQ-MIDEAST-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SUDDENLY, SADDAM FEELS ALONE IN THE ARAB WORLD 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089) 
(bl) 
 By BARBARA CROSSETTE   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNITED NATIONS _ In the uneasy calm that has followed President
Clinton's decision to call off the bombing of Iraq, diplomats
