   _ Football
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCON-FEVER (Atlanta) _ This city has never really loved
them, not the way Cleveland used to love its Browns, when it had
them, or the way Pittsburgh loves the Steelers, and certainly not
the way Green Bay loves its Packers. But then, as the cliche goes,
it is easy to love a winner, even if the trophies have dust on
them. By Rick Bragg. (With a photo.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-KRAFT _ The occasion called for Champagne. Robert
Kraft, the owner of the New England Patriots, had just agreed to
move his football team from Massachusetts to Connecticut. But last
Sunday, Kraft wasn't celebrating. In full-page advertisements in
the Boston newspapers, Kraft offered a 1,400-word apology. ``Make
no mistake,'' he wrote. ``This decision was not easy.'' Kraft
doesn't just want Connecticut's money. He wants to be forgiven for
taking it. By David M. Halbfinger.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Bryan Cox: is the Jets' time
bomb ticking once again? By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SAINTS-COLLINS (Undated) _ The Saints hope Kerry Collins can
turn his troubled life around. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Different paths for Broncos and
Vikings; deal reached over Woodson's refusal. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS (Undated) _ Vinny Testaverde's hot hand comes at the
right time. By Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-GIANTS-STADIUM (Undated) _ Giants Stadium is likely to go
natural, turning turf into grass. By Bill Pennington.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-QUARTERBACKS (Undated) _ College football's year of the
quarterback: a talented group is ready to graduate to the pro game.
By Joe Drape.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-TEXAS-WILLIAMS (Austin) _ Feature folo to Texas-Texas A&AMP;M
game, focusing on Ricky Williams. By Timothy W. Smith.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-SYRACUSE-MIAMI (Syracuse, N.Y.) _ Miami at Syracuse, 3:30
p.m. By Joe Drape.
</P>
