</P>
<P>
   In 19th-century Texas, a spunky woman helps a New Yorker
</P>
<P>
   who has come to revenge his father's murder.
</P>
<P>
   11. THE MACGREGOR GROOMS, by Nora Roberts. (Silhouette,
</P>
<P>
   $6.99.) A patriarch takes steps to get his three
</P>
<P>
   stubbornly single grandsons married.
</P>
<P>
   12. COLD MOUNTAIN, by Charles Frazier. (Vintage, $13.) A wounded
</P>
<P>
   Confederate soldier journeys home toward the end of the Civil
</P>
<P>
   War to meet an old love and a new world.
</P>
<P>
   13. A CERTAIN JUSTICE, by P.D. James. (Ballantine,
</P>
<P>
   $7.99.) Adam Dalgliesh in pursuit of the murderer of
</P>
<P>
   a widely detested criminal lawyer.
</P>
<P>
   14. THE INVESTIGATORS, by W.E.B. Griffin. (Jove, $7.50.)
</P>
<P>
   Philadelphia cops probe crimes committed within their
</P>
<P>
   department and outside it.
</P>
<P>
   15. LITTLE ALTARS EVERYWHERE, by Rebecca Wells. (Harper
</P>
<P>
   Perennial, $13.) An account of earlier experiences of the
</P>
<P>
   Ya-Ya sisterhood.
</P>
<P>
   16.(x) BELOVED, by Toni Morrison. (Plume, $12.95.)
</P>
<P>
   Memories of her past haunt an escaped slave in
</P>
<P>
   post-Civil War Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NON-FICTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE PERFECT STORM, by Sebastian Junger. (Harper Paperbacks,
</P>
<P>
   $6.99.) The story of the nor'easter of 1991, focusing on a
</P>
<P>
   crew of fishermen from Gloucester, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   2. ADVENTURES OF A PSYCHIC, by Sylvia Browne and Antoinette
</P>
<P>
   May. (Hay House, $12.95.) A psychic tells her life story.
</P>
<P>
   3. THE SEAT OF THE SOUL, by Gary Zukav. (Fireside/S&AMP;S,
</P>
<P>
   $12.) How daily activities can be enhanced by feelings
</P>
<P>
   of meaning and purpose.
</P>
<P>
   4. INTO THIN AIR, by Jon Krakauer. (Anchor/Doubleday, $7.99.)
</P>
<P>
   Ascending Mount Everest in 1996, the deadliest season
</P>
<P>
   in history.
</P>
<P>
   5. A CIVIL ACTION, by Jonathan Harr. (Vintage, $13.)
</P>
<P>
   A lawsuit brought by Massachusetts householders against
</P>
<P>
   industrial polluters. (b)
</P>
<P>
   6. THE MILLIONAIRE NEXT DOOR, by Thomas J. Stanley and
</P>
<P>
   William D. Danko. (Pocket, $14.) An analysis of the lives
</P>
<P>
   of wealthy Americans. (b)
</P>
<P>
   7.THE VIRTUES OF AGING, by Jimmy Carter. (Library of
</P>
<P>
   Contemporary Thought/Ballantine, $9.95.) Reflections
</P>
<P>
   on the problems and rewarding opportunities of old
</P>
<P>
   age by the former president.
</P>
<P>
   8. ANATOMY OF THE SPIRIT, by Caroline Myss. (Three Rivers,
</P>
<P>
   $14.) The importance of holistic ``energy medicine.'' (b)
</P>
<P>
   9. UNDER THE TUSCAN SUN, by Frances Mayes.
</P>
<P>
   (Broadway, $13.) A celebration of life in the
</P>
<P>
   Italian countryside.
</P>
<P>
   10. CITIZEN SOLDIERS, by Stephen E. Ambrose. (Touchstone/S&AMP;S,
</P>
<P>
   $16.) The U.S. Army, from Normandy to Germany's
</P>
<P>
   surrender.
</P>
<P>
   11. INTO THE WILD, by Jon Krakauer. (Anchor/Doubleday, $12.95.)
</P>
<P>
   How a young man's obsession with the wilderness
</P>
<P>
   had a tragic end in Alaska.
</P>
<P>
   12. THE HEART AND SOUL OF NICK CARTER, by Jane Carter. (Onyx,
</P>
<P>
   $9.50.) An illustrated biography of the youngest member
</P>
<P>
   of the Backstreet Boys, written by his mother.
</P>
<P>
   13. ALL OVER BUT THE SHOUTIN', by Rick Bragg. (Vintage,
</P>
<P>
   $14.) From poor white in Alabama to Pulitzer Prize-winning
</P>
<P>
   reporter: a memoir.
</P>
<P>
   14. THE COLOR OF WATER, by James McBride. (Riverhead, $12.)
</P>
<P>
   A black writer recalls growing up with his white mother
</P>
<P>
   in Brooklyn.
</P>
<P>
   15.(x) UNDAUNTED COURAGE, by Stephen E. Ambrose. (Touchstone/
</P>
<P>
   S&AMP;S, $16.) Lewis and Clark's exploration of the West. (b)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ADVICE, HOW-TO, AND MISCELLANEOUS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. CHICKEN SOUP FOR THE TEENAGE SOUL II, compiled by Jack
</P>
<P>
   Canfield, Mark Victor Hansen and Kimberly Kirberger.
</P>
<P>
   (Health Communications, $12.95.) Inspirational stories. (b)
</P>
<P>
   2. DR. ATKINS' NEW DIET REVOLUTION, by Robert C. Atkins.
</P>
<P>
   (Avon, $6.50.) Ways to lose weight and achieve a healthy body.
(b)
</P>
<P>
   3. DON'T SWEAT THE SMALL STUFF ... AND IT'S ALL SMALL STUFF,
</P>
<P>
   by Richard Carlson. (Hyperion, $8.95.) How to enjoy life
</P>
<P>
   more and contribute to the world we live in. (b)
</P>
<P>
   4. PROTEIN POWER, by Michael R. Eades and Mary Dan Eades.
</P>
<P>
   (Bantam, $6.50.) A protein-rich, low-carbohydrate plan
</P>
<P>
   for losing weight.
</P>
<P>
   5.(x) CHICKEN SOUP FOR THE TEENAGE SOUL. (Health Communications,
</P>
<P>
   $12.95.) Inspiration. (b)
</P>
